In the mysterious future, crystalline organisms called Gems inhabit a world that has been destroyed by six meteors. Each Gem is assigned a role in order to fight against the Lunarians, a species who attacks them in order to shatter their bodies and use them as decorations.
Phosphophyllite, also known as Phos, is a young and fragile Gem who dreams of helping their friends in the war effort. Instead, they are told to compile an encyclopedia because of their delicate condition. After begrudgingly embarking on this task, Phos meets Cinnabar, an intelligent gem who has been relegated to patrolling the isolated island at night because of the corrosive poison their body creates. After seeing how unhappy Cinnabar is, Phos decides to find a role that both of the rejected Gems can enjoy. Houseki no Kuni follows Phos' efforts to be useful and protect their fellow Gems.

Moriko Morioka is a 30-year-old single NEET woman. After dropping out from reality, she has taken off in search for a fulfilling life and ended up in a net game or "netoge." In the netoge world, she began her new life as a refreshing and handsome character named Hayashi. While starting out as a beginner, a pretty character named Lily reached out to help her. Meanwhile, in the real world, awaits a shocking encounter with a good-looking elite company employee, a mysterious blue-eyed blonde.
(Source: MAL News)

When Sakamoto meets Aoi, the convenience store clerk, it’s love at first sight — and just like that, he retires. Sakamoto gets married, has a daughter, opens a mom-and-pop store in a quiet town, and completely transforms … into a plus-size man. To ensure a peaceful life with his beloved family, the legendary ex–hit man bands together with comrades to face off against the looming threat of assassins. (Source: Netflix TUDUM) Note: The series is streaming a week in advance on Netflix Japan starting with episode 2 released alongside episode 1.

After a traffic accident, 52-year-old civil servant Kenzaburou Tondabayashi awakens to find he's become Grace Auvergne, a duke's daughter, and more importantly the villainess of an otome game. Not wanting to get in the way of the happy endings of the young characters around him, Grace sets out to play the role of the villain, but whether it's due to Kenzaburou's memories of being an affectionate parent getting in the way or not being able to remember those pesky foreign names properly, it ends up being a lot harder than it looks...
Sex ga Suki de Suki de Daisuki na Classmate no Anoko

Episode 1 - 2: Sex ga Suki de Suki de Daisuki na Classmate no Anoko Taichi Sano is short of money and, lured by the high hourly wage, applies for a part-time job as a camera assistant. While he is waiting at the location specified by the employer, his classmate Kanna Hiiragi appears. Kanna has a reputation of being the cutest girl in the school, and many boys confessed their feelings for her. Taichi also harbors a faint hope of dating her, so he hopes that this part-time job will be an opportunity to become closer to her. However, when Taichi finds out that the filming will be for an adult video, he tries to refuse, but Kanna accepts, saying that it will help her learn social studies. Taichi feels happy working part-time with Kanna. The part-time job is going well, although he is nervous about Kanna's occasional bold behavior. However, an accident occurs with the cameraman and actor, and Taichi has to suddenly take over. Kanna ends up doing the filming instead. Episode 3 - 4: Hitori Ecchi:Onanie x2 Nitta is in love with Natsuki Amamori, who sits next to him. However, Natsuki is an honor student and Nitta is not good at studying, so there is no way they can be a match for each other, and she is a girl beyond his reach. What's more, Nitta has a hobby that he can't tell anyone about. He masturbates on Natsuki wherever he goes, even on school grounds. As he was thinking about Natsuki again today, he heard a noise. He peeked in that direction and found Natsuki masturbating. Nitta was transfixed by her. By chance, Natsuki found him. Seeing that she was about to cry after being seen in an embarrassing situation, Nitta confessed that he had been masturbating just a moment ago. (Source: Getchu, translated)

In middle school, Uka Ishimori was nicknamed “Stone.”
In order to change herself, she enrolled in Hachimitsu High School, known for its culture of student liberty. Seated in at the desk next to her in the same class is Kai Miura, a coolly freewheeling boy with lemon-colored hair. In truth, Uka met Kai once in middle school, and decided to attend Hachimitsu based on a single word he said to her.To Uka, the popular Kai is a distant presence.
Yet somehow, Kai starts to look after Uka. With Kai encouraging her, Uka gradually begins to fit in with her classmates…
But...Uka’s world is gradually changing with Kai’s presence. —
Now, I am in the center of the endlessly spreading light.
(Source: Crunchyroll)

After a disastrous defeat at the 2018 World Cup, Japan's team struggles to regroup. But what's missing? An absolute Ace Striker, who can guide them to the win. The Japan Football Union is hell-bent on creating a striker who hungers for goals and thirsts for victory, and who can be the decisive instrument in turning around a losing match...and to do so, they've gathered 300 of Japan's best and brightest youth players. Who will emerge to lead the team...and will they be able to out-muscle and out-ego everyone who stands in their way? (Source: Kodansha USA) Note: Winner of the 45th Kodansha Manga Award in the Shounen Category in 2021.

For the sooty industrial town's lads there's only one point of light: the Light Club, a secret brotherhood they've organized in an abandoned factory. They're on the verge of booting up their crowning achievement, a "thinking machine" fueled by lychee fruits. At the same time, the middle schoolers' cooties-fearing solidarity is devolving into a downright National Socialist muck of murderous paranoia, perverse aestheticism, and (not always) suppressed homosexuality.
(Source: Kodansha USA)
JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken: The JOJOLands

The stage is set on a volcanic island in the Pacific Ocean, Hawaii. Jodio Joestar, a young boy living on Oahu Island, harbors the ambition to become a great millionaire. The clue to his goal lies in reaching the pinnacle of the mechanisms of this world. What means will he choose to achieve his objective?
